### Footnotes

<span id="fn_330"></span>[370:664](1308.htm#fr_330.md) page 1307: It seems
to me probable that this note, which occurs in the note book used in
1502, when Leonardo, in the service of Cesare Borgia, visited Urbino,
was suggested by the famous pillage of the riches of the palace of
Guidobaldo, whose treasures Cesare Borgia at once had carried to Cesena
(see GREGOROVIUS, *Geschichte der Stadt Rom im Mittelalter*. XIII, 5,
4).

